Hi @Kezz101!

It looks like the `invisible-table-row` class name is being added and removed. This does break how tablesorter sorts child rows. So I think the easiest solution would be to add an additional class name for child rows; the default setting is `tablesorter-childRow` in addition to the invisible table row class name ([demo](http://jsfiddle.net/Mottie/d2r0Lgav/)).

Don't use the `cssChildRow` option in this case, and remove the triggered update immediately after tablesorter is initialized - it isn't needed.

```js
$(".tablesorter").tablesorter({
    theme: "bootstrap",
    widthFixed: true,
    headerTemplate: "{content} {icon}",
    // cssChildRow: 'invisible-table-row',
    sortList: [[0,0]],
    widgets: ["uitheme", "filter", "zebra"],
    widgetOptions: {
        zebra: ["even", "odd"],
        filter_reset: ".reset"
    }
});

// tablesorter was just initialized; this code is not needed
// $(".tablesorter").trigger("update", false);
```

And make sure that this css is defined somewhere:

```css
.invisible-table-row {
    display: none;
}
```

To make the fixed column show the correct number of rows, set the pager [`removeRows` option](http://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#pager-removerows) to `true`.

