The returned data structure is essentially a [tree](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tree_(data_structure)). You can traverse it with the common [tree traversal algorithms](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tree_traversal). That way you can decide at run-time what nodes you want to visit.

```python
def traverse(tree):
    for child in tree['children']:
        traverse(child)
    if tree['id'] == 12345:
        print("found")
```

