In case anybody is using nginx and tries to set up *exact* header `Content-Type: text/plain` here is the configuration I used that worked for me:

```nginx
location /.well-known/ {
  default_type text/plain;
  charset off;
}
```
I put this into `server {}`.

Also, redirections did not work for me so I made sure that nginx is serving files *directly* (so no `30x` codes, only `200`).

