Thanks for taking the time to study marshmallow, @sabinem . Marshmallow currently has no hard external dependencies, which keeps the codebase self-contained. This is not to say marshmallow will never have external dependencies--sufficiently stable dependencies that add value will certainly be considered.

Re: OrderedSet--marshmallow already exposes a way to change the set class:

```python
from myorderedset import OrderedSet

class MySchema(Schema):
    @property
    def set_class(self):
        return OrderedSet if self.ordered else set
```

As long we have this hook, I don't think adding a dependency is necessary. It's the same as the `Meta.json_module` option: though there are alternative JSON encoding/decoding libaries (e.g. simplejson, ujson), it suffices to expose an option that lets the user choose.

