So I think there are few ways to go about fixing this. The way that would lead to the quickest fix would be to add some work  in `Display`. The cellMap is an ImmutableJS data structure, to get data from it you use functions that are a part of that library https://facebook.github.io/immutable-js/. 

The code in src/notebook/reducers/document: 
```javascript
[constants.TOGGLE_OUTPUT_EXPANSION]: function toggleOutputExpansion(state, action) {
    const { id } = action;

    return state.updateIn(['notebook', 'cellMap'], (cells) => cells.setIn([id, 'outputExpanded'],
      !cells.getIn([id, 'outputExpanded'])));
```
takes the state of the notebook, and the id of the cell you want to change, and returns a new immutable data structure where the output expanded boolean is the opposite of what it previously was. What you want to do is something similar, but check if the outputExpanded boolean is different, and use that boolean instead. There might be some other fix that is easier and/or more sensible but this should at least point you in some possible direction to go to fix it.

Finished off making autosave based on the _actual_ last modified timestamp. 🎉 

Next piece is tracking when we keep auto save on or off. Originally @yuvipanda and I thought about beginning autosaving once an initial autosave action was been kicked off, just like in the redux-observable 1.0.0 example:

```js
const autoSaveEpic = (action$, state$) =>
  action$.pipe(
    ofType(AUTO_SAVE_ENABLE),
    // The use of an exhaustMap here is basically a flipped switch to say
    // "we are in autosaving mode, don't re-enable it again until requested"
    exhaustMap(() =>
      state$.pipe(
        // Note that our setup is a little more complex because we have multiple documents (potentially)
        // and are autosaving per contentRef
        pluck('content'),
        distinctUntilChanged(),
        throttleTime(500, { leading: false, trailing: true }),
        concatMap(content =>
          saveContent(content).pipe(
            map(() => saveContentFulfilled()),
            catchError(e => of(saveContentRejected(e)))
          )
        ),
        takeUntil(action$.pipe(
          ofType(AUTO_SAVE_DISABLE)
        ))
      )
    )
  );
```

Instead we'd like to store it in the state tree for each content element, and update the state for that field.

